      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:2:37:1",
      "text": [
        " لَا يَتَوَارَثُ رَجُلَانِ قَتَلَ أَحَدُهُمَا صَاحِبَهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Al Husayn Bin Saeed, from Al Qasim Bin Muhammad, from Ali Bin Abu Hamza, from Abu Baseer, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The two men would not inherit when one of them has killed his companion’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "1. A number of our people have narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad ibn ‘Isa from al-Husayn ibn Sa‘id from al-Qasim ibn Muhammad ibn Muhammad from Ali ibn abu Hamzah from abu Basir who has narrated the following: “Abu ‘ Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Two people of whom one has killed the other cannot inherit each other.’” "
        ]
      }
